The paper proposes a novel framework for learning Granger causality from event sequences using neural point processes and attribution methods. This involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks and statistical inference, which are commonly associated with sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing and text analysis, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
